(«k:defvar» «v:write-contents-functions» nil
  «d:"List of functions to be called before writing out a buffer to a file.
If one of them returns non-nil, the file is considered already written
and the rest are not called and neither are the functions in
`«c:write-file-functions»'.

This variable is meant to be used for hooks that pertain to the
buffer's contents, not to the particular visited file; thus,
`«c:set-visited-file-name»' does not clear this variable; but changing the
