(«k:defun» «f:find-file» (filename «t:&optional» wildcards)
  «d:"Edit file FILENAME.
Switch to a buffer visiting file FILENAME,
creating one if none already exists.
Interactively, the default if you just type RET is the current directory,
but the visited file name is available through the minibuffer history:
type M-n to pull it into the minibuffer.

You can visit files on remote machines by specifying something
like /ssh:SOME_REMOTE_MACHINE:FILE for the file name.  You can
also visit local files as a different user by specifying
/sudo::FILE for the file name.
See the Info node `(tramp)File name Syntax' in the Tramp Info
manual, for more about this.

Interactively, or if WILDCARDS is non-nil in a call from Lisp,
expand wildcards (if any) and visit multiple files.  You can
suppress wildcard expansion by setting `«c:find-file-wildcards»' to nil.

To visit a file without any kind of conversion and without
automatically choosing a major mode, use \\[«c:find-file-literally»]."»
  (interactive
   (find-file-read-args «s:"Find file: "»
                        (confirm-nonexistent-file-or-buffer)))
  («k:let» ((value (find-file-noselect filename nil nil wildcards)))
    («k:if» (listp value)
	(mapcar 'switch-to-buffer (nreverse value))
      (switch-to-buffer value))))

(«k:defun» «f:find-file-other-window» (filename «t:&optional» wildcards)
  «d:"Edit file FILENAME, in another window.

Like \\[«c:find-file»] (which see), but creates a new window or reuses
an existing one.  See the function `«c:display-buffer»'.

Interactively, the default if you just type RET is the current directory,
but the visited file name is available through the minibuffer history:
type M-n to pull it into the minibuffer.

Interactively, or if WILDCARDS is non-nil in a call from Lisp,
expand wildcards (if any) and visit multiple files."»
  (interactive
   (find-file-read-args «s:"Find file in other window: "»
                        (confirm-nonexistent-file-or-buffer)))
  («k:let» ((value (find-file-noselect filename nil nil wildcards)))
    («k:if» (listp value)
	(«k:progn»
	  (setq value (nreverse value))
	  (switch-to-buffer-other-window (car value))
	  (mapc 'switch-to-buffer (cdr value))
	  value)
      (switch-to-buffer-other-window value))))

(«k:defun» «f:find-file-other-frame» (filename «t:&optional» wildcards)
  «d:"Edit file FILENAME, in another frame.

Like \\[«c:find-file»] (which see), but creates a new frame or reuses
