«m:;; »«x:Safe local variables:
»«m:;;»«x:
»«m:;; »«x:For variables defined by major modes, the safety declarations can go into
»«m:;; »«x:the major mode's file, since that will be loaded before file variables are
»«m:;; »«x:processed.
»«m:;;»«x:
»«m:;; »«x:For variables defined by minor modes, put the safety declarations in the
»«m:;; »«x:file defining the minor mode after the defcustom/defvar using an autoload
»«m:;; »«x:cookie, e.g.:
»«m:;;»«x:
»«m:;;   »«x:;;;###autoload(put 'variable 'safe-local-variable 'stringp)
»«m:;;»«x:
»«m:;; »«x:Otherwise, when Emacs visits a file specifying that local variable, the
»«m:;; »«x:minor mode file may not be loaded yet.
»«m:;;»«x:
»«m:;; »«x:For variables defined in the C source code the declaration should go here:
»
(«k:dolist» (pair
	 '((buffer-read-only        . booleanp)	«m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (default-directory       . stringp)	«m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (fill-column             . integerp)	«m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (indent-tabs-mode        . booleanp)	«m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (left-margin             . integerp)	«m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (no-update-autoloads     . booleanp)
	   (lexical-binding	 . booleanp)	  «m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (tab-width               . integerp)	  «m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (truncate-lines          . booleanp)	  «m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (word-wrap               . booleanp)	  «m:;; »«x:C source code
»	   (bidi-display-reordering . booleanp))) «m:;; »«x:C source code
»  (put (car pair) 'safe-local-variable (cdr pair)))

